attributes.Long form description: The student disassembles a rolling cart, first unscrews the top tray brackets and removes the top tray, then unscrews the middle tray brackets and removes the middle tray, then unscrews the bottom tray brackets and removes the bottom tray, unscrews the rims and sidebars and finally the base frame.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the top tray.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: When removing the hexagon cap nut, the tray fell, this generated confusion in the student about if she should finish the action or pick up what fell.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the tray in the middle.
The student disassembles the bottom tray.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The hex cap nut was too tight so he had to grab the wrench
The student tries to align the trays but they are misplaced.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the bottom sidebar.
The student disassembles the bottom left side bar.
The student disassembles the bottom right sidebar.
The student disassembles the base frame.
